This paper describes a semantic wiki system that uses natural language processing and controlled natural language grammar to enable multilingual access to wiki content. The paper discusses the use of Attempto Controlled English (ACE) and Grammatical Framework (GF) to achieve this goal. Given the focus on natural language processing and knowledge representation, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.LG. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the wiki system for building and querying knowledge bases, which suggests a connection to cs.DB. Finally, the paper discusses the collaborative editing of the underlying grammar, which suggests a connection to cs.SE.
